rComments: Perfect teacher, very patient and gives very good explainations.

Un des cours les plus intéressants du JD, et comment fondamental. La matière est très intéressante et bien organisée - ce qui fait changement. J'ai particulièrement apprécié la comparaison systématique entre les règles de common law et les articles du Code civil: ca permet de mettre les choses en perspective. Bon cours, bon prof. À prendre!

Cannot teach - she uses circular reasoning - comments on a theme that we need to understand, but then refuses to explain when we do not understand the comparison.  Gets confused between common law and civil law terminology.  Speaks very slowly - the class could be taught in 3 full classes if she were to speed up.
